<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Regular-Expression on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/regular-expression/</link><description>Recent content in Regular-Expression on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/regular-expression/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Regular expression error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/perl/regex-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/perl/regex-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A regex error is raised when a regular expression pattern is malformed, contains invalid syntax, or encounters an error during compilation or matching. Perl&amp;rsquo;s regex engine provides detailed error messages to help identify the issue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unclosed regex delimiters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invalid escape sequences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unbalanced parentheses in pattern&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invalid quantifiers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-perl" data-lang="perl"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Unclosed regex&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; $str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ($str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; /hello/&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# missing closing /&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;match\n&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Balance delimiters&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; $str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ($str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; /hello/&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;match\n&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-perl" data-lang="perl"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Invalid escape&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; $str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ($str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; /\p{L}/&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# may need unicode support&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;match\n&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Use valid pattern or enable features&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; utf8;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; feature &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;unicode_strings&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ($str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; /\p{Letter}/&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;match\n&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-perl" data-lang="perl"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: Unclosed parenthesis&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; $str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; /(hello/&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# unmatched ( in regex&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Invalid quantifier&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; $str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; /hello**/&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# *+ follows nothing in regex&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 3: Invalid character class&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; $str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; /[hello/&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# missing ]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/perl/syntax-error6"&gt;syntax error at line X&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/perl/reference-error"&gt;Can&amp;rsquo;t use string as HASH&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::regex_error — Invalid Regular Expression Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/regex-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/regex-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdregex_error--invalid-regular-expression-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::regex_error — Invalid Regular Expression Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::regex_error&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a regular expression is malformed or uses unsupported syntax for the current grammar flag. This occurs during pattern construction or matching when the regex engine encounters invalid syntax such as unmatched parentheses, invalid escape sequences, or misplaced quantifiers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdregex_error-occurs"&gt;Why std::regex_error Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include unmatched parentheses or brackets, invalid escape sequences, misplaced quantifiers (e.g., &lt;code&gt;*&lt;/code&gt; at the start), unsupported regex features for the chosen grammar, and empty patterns with quantifiers.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::regex_error — Invalid Regular Expression Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/regexerror/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/regexerror/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdregex_error--invalid-regular-expression-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::regex_error — Invalid Regular Expression Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::regex_error&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a regular expression is malformed or uses unsupported syntax for the current grammar flag. This occurs during pattern construction or matching when the regex engine encounters invalid syntax such as unmatched parentheses, invalid escape sequences, or misplaced quantifiers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdregex_error-occurs"&gt;Why std::regex_error Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include unmatched parentheses or brackets, invalid escape sequences, misplaced quantifiers (e.g., &lt;code&gt;*&lt;/code&gt; at the start), unsupported regex features for the chosen grammar, and empty patterns with quantifiers.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>